# Instrument Session Capture with a Change Ledger

## Question

Implement the capture contract from the [session-edge feasibility memo](../../../../joelclaw-wiki/.brain/session-edge-feasibility.svx) so session→page change-edges become deterministically derivable:

- An append-only normalized change ledger emitted at capture time: sessionId, runtime, machineId, repo + worktree identity + starting HEAD, successful mutation tool calls with canonical repo-relative paths and pre/post blob hashes, worktree diffing for bulk shell/generator mutations (never parse command text), immutable `changeSetId`, commit-attribution events carrying `changeSetId` + contributing sessionIds + SHA, uncommitted/superseded markers, and amend/squash/rebase lineage.
- Where it lands is part of the work: the Pi/Claude/Codex capture pipeline (pi extensions, hooks, or the joelclaw session-capture path) — scope the smallest slice that covers Pi first if all three runtimes is too big for one session.
- The consumer is known and waiting: graph schema v3 `session-change` edges, joined by `changeSetId` equality + blob-hash verification.

Executes outside the wiki repo (capture infra, likely joelclaw/pi-tools) — coordinate with whatever session-capture sessions are active on this machine before touching shared pipelines. Resolved when a real day's ledger exists on disk and a re-run of the feasibility check flips its verdict for at least one runtime.
